		"ItemTooltips"
		{
			"item_blink"		"Use Blink Dagger to initiate. Without Blink Dagger, Wraith King won't be able to take advantage of the duration of his stun and may get kited before being able to finish them.

Ultimately, you want to initiate with Blink Dagger and force the enemy team to fight you to activate your ultimate's slow."
			"item_magic_wand"		"Magic Wand is essential for Wraith King who needs to ensure he has enough mana for Reincarnation in the middle of a fight. Whether having your mana burned or simply using it for your great stun: Magic Wand is too good of an item for a hero that gets in the middle of a fight."
			"item_hand_of_midas"		"For your early-farm. Hand of Midas can be situationally good depending on your lane and if you are truly aiming for the late-game. Hand of Midas let's you ensure consistent gold per minute."
			"item_echo_sabre"		"Echo Sabre is a great item for Wraith King, but may not be necessary considering the larger items you may want. As you engage with Wraith King; the stun and slow you can initiate with overlaps with Echo Sabre. "
			"item_assault"		"Assault Cuirass is a more team-based item and can be more ideal than Mjollnir depending your line-up. The armor buff/debuff works well with his constant presence and the attack speed is just right. "
			"item_black_king_bar"		"Use this ability after you reincarnate. You will be able to tank all the stuns they inflict on you. With your ultimate's slow and then your Black King Bar, you will be unstoppable."
			"item_blade_mail"		"The issue with Wraith King is that you'll get kited  a lot.  Blade Mail let's you return the damage and keeps you in the playing field, contributing.

Get Blade Mail after Blink Dagger but don't bother if enemies will be getting Black King Bar."
			"item_radiance"		"Radiance is a unique item for Wraith King where it forces enemies to fight you or perish to your burning Radiance.

However, the cost of it and the need to rush it may require planning. Follow this up with other items like Blink Dagger and Blade Mail - furthering Wraith King's presence."
			"item_armlet"		"Stronger critical strikes, more speed, armor and strength. This is an overall good item. If you die and your ultimate activates, be sure to activate this. 

The life drain from this ability is removed thanks to your own inherent passive lifesteal."
			"item_mjollnir"		"Mjllonir is a great item to give Wraith King further damage, further speed and even more opportunity to return damage when he is getting kited.

Use the Static Charge to punish enemies who target you while making your attacks even more deadly in team-fights."
			"item_desolator"		"Get Desolator to make the few hits you can get in, be the ones that count. Desolator is to help push towers, destroy enemies and reduce their armour while also making Roshan an easy kill."
			"item_abyssal_blade"		"Abyssal Blade keeps foes in place, dishes immense damage and works as a great follow-up with your Blink Dagger, opening up more opportunities for your own Wraithfire Blast"
			"item_sphere"		"Consider Linken's Sphere if specific ultimate, target abilities like stuns and silences are keeping you down. This should be seen different as Black King Bar because it will waste ultimate abilities on you like Doom's Doom or Necrophos' Reaper Scythe from completely killing/disabling you.
"
